\f0\fs24 \cf0 This document describes how to use the snowflake method template for Scrivener.\
In case you\'92re not familiar with the snowflake method, it is a method designed by Randy Ingermanson that helps you go from the broad strokes to the details when you approach your novel so you don\'92t get lost along the way.\
It is called the snowflake method because you start with a very rough shape of your story and as you keep going along you refine that shape more and more and figuratively speaking convert your rough shape into a snowflake form over time with all the tiny details that make it interesting and worth reading.\
I\'92m assuming that you\'92re somewhat familiar with the snowflake method itself. I will not explain it in detail here.\
If you want to know more about the snowflake method, go to {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.advancedfictionwriting.com/articles/snowflake-method/"}}{\fldrslt https://www.advancedfictionwriting.com/articles/snowflake-method/}}.\
Okay, let\'92s get started.\
